    "breadcrumb": "docs.plakar.io \u003e  Commands \u003e  Plakar \u003e  developers branch",
    "content": "PLAKAR-DIGEST(1) General Commands Manual PLAKAR-DIGEST(1) NAME plakar-digest — Compute digests for files in a Plakar snapshot\nSYNOPSIS plakar digest [-hashing algorithm] snapshotID[:path] [...] DESCRIPTION The plakar digest command computes and displays digests for specified path in a the given snapshotID. Multiple snapshotID and path may be given. By default, the command computes the digest by reading the file contents.\nThe options are as follows:\n-hashing algorithm Use algorithm to compute the digest. Defaults to SHA256. EXAMPLES Compute the digest of a file within a snapshot:\n$ plakar digest abc123:/etc/passwd Use BLAKE3 as the digest algorithm:\n$ plakar digest -hashing BLAKE3 abc123:/etc/netstart DIAGNOSTICS The plakar-digest utility exits 0 on success, and \u003e0 if an error occurs.\n0 Command completed successfully. \u003e0 An error occurred, such as failure to retrieve a file digest or invalid snapshot ID. SEE ALSO plakar(1)\nPlakar July 3, 2025 PLAKAR-DIGEST(1)",
