    "content": "PLAKAR-DIGEST(1) - General Commands Manual\nNAME plakar digest - Compute digests for files in a Plakar snapshot\nSYNOPSIS plakar digest [-hashing algorithm] snapshotID[:path] […]\nDESCRIPTION The plakar digest command computes and displays digests for specified path in a the given snapshotID. Multiple snapshotID and path may be given. By default, the command computes the digest by reading the file contents.\nThe options are as follows:\n-hashing algorithm\nUse algorithm to compute the digest. Defaults to SHA256.\nEXAMPLES Compute the digest of a file within a snapshot:\n$ plakar digest abc123:/etc/passwd Use BLAKE3 as the digest algorithm:\n$ plakar digest -hashing BLAKE3 abc123:/etc/netstart DIAGNOSTICS The plakar digest utility exits 0 on success, and \u003e0 if an error occurs.\n0\nCommand completed successfully.\n\u003e0\nAn error occurred, such as failure to retrieve a file digest or invalid snapshot ID.\nSEE ALSO plakar(1)\nPlakar - March 3, 2025",
